<subSubSection id="C322B8883A07FF9EFF0AED60FD84FCDC" pageId="7" pageNumber="1140" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8B87EB033A07FF9EFF0AED60FD84FCDC" blockId="7.[178,1086,545,772]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1140">
Comment: The identity of 
<taxonomicName id="4C3890803A07FF9EFDB4ED63FD3BFDEE" authorityName="PEYERIMHOFF" authorityYear="1929" box="[524,653,545,567]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Lithocharis" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="1140" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="fontinalis">
<emphasis id="B94C37113A07FF9EFDB4ED63FD3BFDEE" box="[524,653,545,567]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="1140">L. fontinalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is doubtful. The original description is based on a unique 
<typeStatus id="548355A13A07FF9EFE31ED7FFE54FD8C" box="[393,482,574,596]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1140">holotype</typeStatus>
from &quot;Hoggar: source T'abor, à quelques kilomtres de 
<collectingRegion id="49FC25E13A07FF9EFF0AED1DFE82FDA9" box="[178,308,604,625]" country="Algeria" name="Tamanghasset" pageId="7" pageNumber="1140">Tamanrasset</collectingRegion>
&quot; sent to him by &quot;M. Pierre Bordes, Gouverneur général de l'Algérie&quot; (
<bibRefCitation id="EFA996F23A07FF9EFF01ED38FE31FD57" author="PEYERIMHOFF P" box="[185,391,633,655]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1140" pagination="53 - 56" refId="ref28741" refString="PEYERIMHOFF P. M. DE (1929): Nouveaux Coleopteres du Nord-Africain soixante-quatrieme note: Faune du Hoggar et des massif voisins. - Bulletin de la Societe Entomologique de France 1929: 53 - 56." type="journal article" year="1929">PEYERIMHOFF 1929</bibRefCitation>
). The male sexual characters are not described, suggesting that the specimen is a female. According to the curator in charge at the MNHNP, the 
<typeStatus id="548355A13A07FF9EFC5DEDD7FB88FD74" box="[997,1086,662,684]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1140">holotype</typeStatus>
was not found in the Peyerimhoff collection (TAGHAVIAN e-mail 
<date id="FF86CDC33A07FF9EFCC8EDF5FC63FD12" box="[880,981,692,714]" pageId="7" pageNumber="1140" value="2014-01-27">27.I.2014</date>
). Thus, it seems that Peyerimhoff returned it to Pierre Bordes. I have been unable to trace the whereabouts of the Bordes collection.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
